<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Tanah Rata</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Main highland village. Cameron Highlands Resort (1937) is the Tudor-style colonial centerpiece. The Jim Thompson Trail commemorates the American Thai-silk king who vanished without trace from a walk in these hills in 1967.]]></description><Point><coordinates>101.382500,4.469100,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>BOH Sungei Palas</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Largest of the BOH (Best of the Highlands) tea plantations, planted from 1929. Free factory tour ending at a tea-room cantilevered over the slope, where you drink the morning's pluck looking down the terraces.]]></description><Point><coordinates>101.391700,4.486000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mossy Forest / Gunung Brinchang</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[2,032 m. A boardwalk on stilts winds through a cloud-forest where every branch and trunk is wrapped in moss, ferns, and pitcher plants. Open early morning before the cloud closes in.]]></description><Point><coordinates>101.390800,4.518900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Kampung Raja</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Wholesale market for the highland vegetable industry — Malaysia's brassicas, lettuces, and strawberries are largely from these greenhouses. Cabbages stacked into pyramids; the smell is overwhelming.]]></description><Point><coordinates>101.373900,4.640300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Ipoh</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Off the loop but worth the descent. Limestone hills riddled with cave temples (Sam Poh Tong, Kek Lok Tong, Perak Tong). Old-town heritage architecture; white-coffee street stalls; one of the great Malaysian food cities.]]></description><Point><coordinates>101.090100,4.597500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
